{"id":"mb3geo-new-530","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"A golden ratio is approximately:","options":["1.618","1.414","3.14159","2.718"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The golden ratio φ ≈ 1.618."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-531","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"A snail travels 0.03 mph. How far does it travel in 5 hours?","options":["0.15 miles","0.15 km","0.003 miles","1.5 miles"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"0.03 × 5 = 0.15 miles."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-532","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"Ratio of blue to total in a pie chart showing 40% blue is:","options":["2:5","3:5","4:5","1:5"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"40% = 40:100 = 2:5."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-533","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"A tank fills in 6 hours. Pipe A alone takes 12 hours and Pipe B alone takes 12 hours. Working together, how long?","options":["6 hours","3 hours","12 hours","4 hours"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"1/12 + 1/12 = 2/12 = 1/6 per hour; 6 hours total."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-534","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"In the ratio 5:3, the second quantity is 15. What is the first?","options":["25","9","10","45"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"5/3 = x/15; x = 25."},
