{"id":"mb3geo-new-538","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"In similar polygons with ratio 3:7, if the smaller area is 18, what is the larger's area?","options":["98","42","126","147"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Area ratio = (3:7)² = 9:49; 18 × 49/9 = 98."},
