{"id":"mb3geo-new-540","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"If x varies directly with y and x=6 when y=9, what is x when y=15?","options":["10","12","20","6"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"k = x/y = 6/9 = 2/3; x = (2/3)(15) = 10."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-541","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"Two gears have 12 and 20 teeth. The smaller turns at 100 rpm. How fast is the larger?","options":["60 rpm","150 rpm","240 rpm","40 rpm"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"12×100 = 20×r; r = 60 rpm (inverse proportion)."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-542","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"Express 2:3 as a percentage of the whole.","options":["40%","60%","66.7%","33.3%"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"2/(2+3) = 2/5 = 40% of the whole."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-543","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"A 20 cm stick casts a 30 cm shadow. A nearby pole casts a 4.5 m shadow. How tall is the pole?","options":["3 m","2 m","6 m","1.5 m"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"20/30 = h/450; h = 300 cm = 3 m."},
