{"id":"mb3geo-new-548","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"Ratio of areas of two similar triangles is 4:9. Ratio of their corresponding sides is:","options":["2:3","4:9","16:81","1:3"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Side ratio = √(4:9) = 2:3."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-549","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"A project needs to be split 3:2 between A and B. If B gets 8 hours, how many does A get?","options":["12","6","10","15"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"3/2 = A/8; A = 12."},
{"id":"mb3geo-new-550","subject":"math","level":"MB3","gradeRange":"Grades 6-8","topic":"Ratios – Advanced","question":"If a rectangle's length and width are in a 5:3 ratio and perimeter is 64, what is the length?","options":["20","12","25","15"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"2(5k+3k) = 64; 16k=64; k=4; length=20."},

